import cv2
import numpy as np
import torch
from torchvision import datasets, transforms
from torch.utils.data import DataLoader

# --- 1) CLAHE transform (for X-rays) ---
class CLAHETransform:
    def __init__(self, clip_limit=2.0, tile_grid_size=(8, 8), p=1.0):
        self.clip_limit = clip_limit
        self.tile_grid_size = tile_grid_size
        self.p = p

    def __call__(self, img):
        # img is a PIL image
        if np.random.rand() > self.p:
            return img

        x = np.array(img)  # RGB or grayscale
        if x.ndim == 3:
            x = cv2.cvtColor(x, cv2.COLOR_RGB2GRAY)

        clahe = cv2.createCLAHE(clipLimit=self.clip_limit, tileGridSize=self.tile_grid_size)
        x = clahe.apply(x)

        # Convert back to 3-channel for pretrained CNNs
        x = cv2.cvtColor(x, cv2.COLOR_GRAY2RGB)
        return transforms.ToPILImage()(x)

# --- 2) Optional denoise transform (mild) ---
class MildDenoise:
    def __init__(self, p=0.2):
        self.p = p

    def __call__(self, img):
        if np.random.rand() > self.p:
            return img
        x = np.array(img)
        # Median filter (good mild denoise)
        x = cv2.medianBlur(x, 3)
        return transforms.ToPILImage()(x)

# --- 3) Train transforms (augmentation + CLAHE + normalization) ---
train_tfms = transforms.Compose([
    transforms.Resize((224, 224)),
    CLAHETransform(clip_limit=2.0, tile_grid_size=(8,8), p=1.0),  # always apply
    MildDenoise(p=0.2),  # apply sometimes
    transforms.RandomRotation(degrees=10),
    transforms.RandomResizedCrop(224, scale=(0.9, 1.0)),
    transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(p=0.5),
    transforms.ColorJitter(brightness=0.08, contrast=0.12),
    transforms.ToTensor(),
    transforms.Normalize(mean=[0.485,0.456,0.406], std=[0.229,0.224,0.225]),
])

# --- 4) Val/test transforms (NO augmentation; keep CLAHE + normalization only) ---
val_tfms = transforms.Compose([
    transforms.Resize((224, 224)),
    CLAHETransform(clip_limit=2.0, tile_grid_size=(8,8), p=1.0),
    transforms.ToTensor(),
    transforms.Normalize(mean=[0.485,0.456,0.406], std=[0.229,0.224,0.225]),
])

def ensure_val_split(data_dir, val_ratio=0.15):
    data_dir = Path(data_dir)
    train_dir = data_dir / "train"
    val_dir = data_dir / "val"
    test_dir = data_dir / "test"

    assert train_dir.exists(), f"Missing train folder: {train_dir}"
    assert test_dir.exists(),  f"Missing test folder: {test_dir}"

    # If val exists and has content, do nothing
    if val_dir.exists() and any(val_dir.rglob("*.*")):
        print(" Validation folder already exists:", val_dir)
        return

    print(" val/ not found or empty. Creating validation split from train/ ...")
    (val_dir / "NORMAL").mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
    (val_dir / "PNEUMONIA").mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

    for cls in ["NORMAL", "PNEUMONIA"]:
        cls_train = train_dir / cls
        files = [p for p in cls_train.iterdir() if p.suffix.lower() in [".jpeg", ".jpg", ".png"]]
        random.shuffle(files)

        n_val = max(1, int(len(files) * val_ratio))
        val_files = files[:n_val]

        for p in val_files:
            dest = val_dir / cls / p.name
            shutil.move(str(p), str(dest))

    print(" Created val split at:", val_dir)

ensure_val_split(DATA_DIR, val_ratio=0.15)

import torch

class LungSegDataset(torch.utils.data.Dataset):
    """
    Minimal wrapper so notebook runs.
    (No real masking yet; just forwards through transforms.)
    """
    def __init__(self, base_dataset, transform=None, cache_dir=None, cache_masks=True):
        self.base = base_dataset
        self.transform = transform

        #  expose ImageFolder attributes so downstream code works
        self.targets = getattr(base_dataset, "targets", None)
        self.class_to_idx = getattr(base_dataset, "class_to_idx", None)

    def __len__(self):
        return len(self.base)

    def __getitem__(self, idx):
        img, label = self.base[idx]  # PIL image, int label
        if self.transform:
            img = self.transform(img)
        return img, label

def compute_class_weights(imagefolder_ds):
    # counts per class index
    targets = np.array(imagefolder_ds.targets)
    counts = np.bincount(targets)
    weights = 1.0 / (counts + 1e-9)
    weights = weights / weights.sum() * len(counts)
    return torch.tensor(weights, dtype=torch.float32)

class_weights = compute_class_weights(train_ds).to(device)
print("Class weights:", class_weights.detach().cpu().numpy())

class SmallCNN(nn.Module):
    """Sequential-style baseline in PyTorch."""
    def __init__(self, num_classes=2):
        super().__init__()

        self.features = nn.Sequential(

            nn.Conv2d(3, 32, 3, padding=1),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.MaxPool2d(2),

            nn.Conv2d(32, 64, 3, padding=1),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.MaxPool2d(2),

            nn.Conv2d(64, 128, 3, padding=1),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.MaxPool2d(2),

            nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d((1,1)),
        )

        self.classifier = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Flatten(),
            nn.Dropout(0.2),
            nn.Linear(128, num_classes)
        )

    def forward(self, x):
        return self.classifier(self.features(x))


def make_model(name, num_classes=2):

    name = name.lower()

    # --------------------
    # BASELINE
    # --------------------
    if name == "smallcnn":
        return SmallCNN(num_classes=num_classes)


    # --------------------
    # RESNET
    # --------------------
    if name == "resnet18":
        m = models.resnet18(
            weights=models.ResNet18_Weights.DEFAULT
        )
        m.fc = nn.Linear(
            m.fc.in_features,
            num_classes
        )
        return m


    if name == "resnet50":
        m = models.resnet50(
            weights=models.ResNet50_Weights.DEFAULT
        )
        m.fc = nn.Linear(
            m.fc.in_features,
            num_classes
        )
        return m


    # --------------------
    # EFFICIENTNET
    # --------------------
    if name == "efficientnet_b0":
        m = models.efficientnet_b0(
            weights=models.EfficientNet_B0_Weights.DEFAULT
        )
        m.classifier[1] = nn.Linear(
            m.classifier[1].in_features,
            num_classes
        )
        return m


    if name == "efficientnet_b3":
        m = models.efficientnet_b3(
            weights=models.EfficientNet_B3_Weights.DEFAULT
        )
        m.classifier[1] = nn.Linear(
            m.classifier[1].in_features,
            num_classes
        )
        return m


    if name == "efficientnet_b4":
        m = models.efficientnet_b4(
            weights=models.EfficientNet_B4_Weights.DEFAULT
        )
        m.classifier[1] = nn.Linear(
            m.classifier[1].in_features,
            num_classes
        )
        return m


    # --------------------
    # CONVNEXT
    # --------------------
    if name == "convnext_tiny":
        m = models.convnext_tiny(
            weights=models.ConvNeXt_Tiny_Weights.DEFAULT
        )
        m.classifier[2] = nn.Linear(
            m.classifier[2].in_features,
            num_classes
        )
        return m


    if name == "convnext_small":
        m = models.convnext_small(
            weights=models.ConvNeXt_Small_Weights.DEFAULT
        )
        m.classifier[2] = nn.Linear(
            m.classifier[2].in_features,
            num_classes
        )
        return m


    if name == "convnext_base":
        m = models.convnext_base(
            weights=models.ConvNeXt_Base_Weights.DEFAULT
        )
        m.classifier[2] = nn.Linear(
            m.classifier[2].in_features,
            num_classes
        )
        return m


    # --------------------
    # SWIN TRANSFORMER
    # --------------------
    if name == "swin_t":
        m = models.swin_t(
            weights=models.Swin_T_Weights.DEFAULT
        )
        m.head = nn.Linear(
            m.head.in_features,
            num_classes
        )
        return m


    if name == "swin_s":
        m = models.swin_s(
            weights=models.Swin_S_Weights.DEFAULT
        )
        m.head = nn.Linear(
            m.head.in_features,
            num_classes
        )
        return m


    # --------------------
    # DENSENET
    # --------------------
    if name == "densenet121":
        m = models.densenet121(
            weights=models.DenseNet121_Weights.DEFAULT
        )
        m.classifier = nn.Linear(
            m.classifier.in_features,
            num_classes
        )
        return m


    raise ValueError(f"Unknown model name: {name}")

# -------------------------------
# 7) TRAIN + EVAL UTILITIES
# -------------------------------
def run_one_epoch(model, loader, optimizer, criterion, scaler=None, train=True):
    model.train(train)
    total_loss = 0.0
    correct = 0
    total = 0

    for x, y in loader:
        x = x.to(device, non_blocking=True)
        y = y.to(device, non_blocking=True)

        if train:
            optimizer.zero_grad(set_to_none=True)

        with torch.cuda.amp.autocast(enabled=(scaler is not None)):
            logits = model(x)
            loss = criterion(logits, y)

        if train:
            if scaler is not None:
                scaler.scale(loss).backward()
                scaler.step(optimizer)
                scaler.update()
            else:
                loss.backward()
                optimizer.step()

        total_loss += loss.item() * x.size(0)
        preds = logits.argmax(dim=1)
        correct += (preds == y).sum().item()
        total += x.size(0)

    return total_loss / max(total,1), correct / max(total,1)

@torch.no_grad()
def predict_probs(model, loader):
    model.eval()
    y_true, y_prob = [], []
    for x, y in loader:
        x = x.to(device, non_blocking=True)
        logits = model(x)
        prob = torch.softmax(logits, dim=1)[:, 1]  # pneumonia prob
        y_true.extend(y.numpy().tolist())
        y_prob.extend(prob.detach().cpu().numpy().tolist())
    return np.array(y_true), np.array(y_prob)

def evaluate_metrics(y_true, y_prob, thr=0.5):
    y_pred = (y_prob >= thr).astype(int)
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = cm.ravel()

    acc = (tp+tn)/(tp+tn+fp+fn+1e-9)
    prec = tp/(tp+fp+1e-9)
    rec = tp/(tp+fn+1e-9)
    spec = tn/(tn+fp+1e-9)
    f1 = 2*prec*rec/(prec+rec+1e-9)

    roc = roc_auc_score(y_true, y_prob) if len(np.unique(y_true))==2 else None
    pr  = average_precision_score(y_true, y_prob) if len(np.unique(y_true))==2 else None

    rep_txt = classification_report(y_true, y_pred, target_names=["NORMAL","PNEUMONIA"], digits=4)
    rep_dict = classification_report(y_true, y_pred, target_names=["NORMAL","PNEUMONIA"], output_dict=True)

    return {
        "Accuracy": float(acc),
        "Precision": float(prec),
        "Recall": float(rec),
        "Specificity": float(spec),
        "F1": float(f1),
        "ROC_AUC": None if roc is None else float(roc),
        "PR_AUC": None if pr is None else float(pr),
        "TN": int(tn), "FP": int(fp), "FN": int(fn), "TP": int(tp),
        "ConfusionMatrix": cm.tolist(),
        "ReportText": rep_txt,
        "ReportDict": rep_dict
    }

def train_model_experiment(model_name):
    model = make_model(model_name, num_classes=2).to(device)

    criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss(weight=class_weights if cfg.use_class_weights else None)
    optimizer = torch.optim.AdamW(model.parameters(), lr=cfg.lr, weight_decay=cfg.weight_decay)
    scaler = torch.cuda.amp.GradScaler(enabled=(cfg.use_amp and device=="cuda"))

    best_f1 = -1
    best_path = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, f"{model_name}_best.pt")

    print(f"\n====================== TRAINING: {model_name} ======================")
    for epoch in range(1, cfg.epochs+1):
        t0 = time.time()
        tr_loss, tr_acc = run_one_epoch(model, train_loader, optimizer, criterion, scaler=scaler, train=True)
        va_loss, va_acc = run_one_epoch(model, val_loader, optimizer, criterion, scaler=None, train=False)

        # evaluate val F1 @0.5
        y_true, y_prob = predict_probs(model, val_loader)
        val_metrics = evaluate_metrics(y_true, y_prob, thr=0.5)

        if val_metrics["F1"] > best_f1:
            best_f1 = val_metrics["F1"]
            torch.save({
                "model_name": model_name,
                "state_dict": model.state_dict(),
                "cfg": cfg.__dict__
            }, best_path)

        print(f"Epoch {epoch:02d}/{cfg.epochs} | "
              f"train loss {tr_loss:.4f} acc {tr_acc:.4f} | "
              f"val loss {va_loss:.4f} acc {va_acc:.4f} | "
              f"val [email protected] {val_metrics['F1']:.4f} | "
              f"time {time.time()-t0:.1f}s | bestF1 {best_f1:.4f}")

    # load best
    ckpt = torch.load(best_path, map_location=device)
    model.load_state_dict(ckpt["state_dict"])
    model.eval()

    # test eval
    y_true_t, y_prob_t = predict_probs(model, test_loader)
    test_metrics = evaluate_metrics(y_true_t, y_prob_t, thr=0.5)

    return best_path, test_metrics

import gc
import torch
import pandas as pd
import os

experiments = [
    "smallcnn",
    "resnet18",
    "resnet50",
    "efficientnet_b0",
    "efficientnet_b3",
    # "efficientnet_b4",   # keep commented on T4
    "convnext_tiny",
    "convnext_small",
    "swin_t",
    "swin_s",
    "densenet121",
]

results = []
reports = {}

for mname in experiments:
    print("\n===============================")
    print("TRAINING:", mname)
    print("===============================\n")

    try:
        best_path, metrics = train_model_experiment(mname)

        #  append ONLY ONCE
        results.append({
            "Model": mname,
            "Checkpoint": best_path,
            "Accuracy": metrics["Accuracy"],
            "Precision": metrics["Precision"],
            "Recall": metrics["Recall"],
            "Specificity": metrics["Specificity"],
            "F1": metrics["F1"],
            "ROC_AUC": metrics["ROC_AUC"],
            "PR_AUC": metrics["PR_AUC"],
            "TN": metrics["TN"],
            "FP": metrics["FP"],
            "FN": metrics["FN"],
            "TP": metrics["TP"],
        })

        # save report text (use the exact key your function returns)
        reports[mname] = metrics.get("ReportText", metrics.get("ReportText1", ""))

    except RuntimeError as e:
        if "out of memory" in str(e).lower():
            print(f" CUDA OOM for {mname}. Skipping this model.")
        else:
            raise

    finally:
        gc.collect()
        torch.cuda.empty_cache()

#  AFTER the loop: create df + save CSV once
df = pd.DataFrame(results).sort_values("F1", ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)
csv_path = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, "model_comparison.csv")
df.to_csv(csv_path, index=False)

print("\n================ FINAL MODEL COMPARISON (Test @0.5) ================")
print(df)
print("\n Saved comparison CSV:", csv_path)

print("\n================ CLASSIFICATION REPORTS (Test) ================")
for m in df["Model"].tolist():
    print(f"\n--- {m} ---")
    print(reports.get(m, "(no report text found)"))

print("\n All outputs in:", OUTPUT_DIR)

import numpy as np
from tqdm import tqdm

def get_probs_labels(dataloader, model):
    model.eval()
    y_true, y_prob = [], []
    with torch.no_grad():
        for x, y in tqdm(dataloader, desc="Predicting"):
            x = x.to(device)
            y = y.to(device)
            logits = model(x)
            probs = F.softmax(logits, dim=1)[:, 1]  # probability of class=1 (PNEUMONIA)
            y_true.append(y.detach().cpu().numpy())
            y_prob.append(probs.detach().cpu().numpy())
    y_true = np.concatenate(y_true)
    y_prob = np.concatenate(y_prob)
    return y_true, y_prob

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix

os.makedirs(OUTPUT_DIR, exist_ok=True)

# Class labels (INSERT THIS)
CLASS_NAMES = ["NORMAL", "PNEUMONIA"]

def save_confusion_matrix(y_true, y_prob, out_path, thresh=0.5, class_names=CLASS_NAMES):
    y_pred = (y_prob >= thresh).astype(int)
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)

    plt.figure()
    plt.imshow(cm)
    plt.title(f"Confusion Matrix (thresh={thresh})")
    plt.xlabel("Predicted")
    plt.ylabel("True")
    plt.xticks([0,1], class_names)
    plt.yticks([0,1], class_names)

    # annotate
    for i in range(cm.shape[0]):
        for j in range(cm.shape[1]):
            plt.text(j, i, str(cm[i, j]), ha="center", va="center")

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(out_path, dpi=200)
    plt.show()
    return cm

from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc

def save_roc(y_true, y_prob, out_path):
    fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_true, y_prob)
    roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)

    plt.figure()
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f"AUC={roc_auc:.4f}")
    plt.plot([0,1], [0,1], linestyle="--")
    plt.title("ROC Curve")
    plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate")
    plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate")
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(out_path, dpi=200)
    plt.show()
    return roc_auc

roc_path = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, f"{best_model_name}_roc.png")

from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_curve, average_precision_score

def save_pr(y_true, y_prob, out_path):
    precision, recall, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_true, y_prob)
    ap = average_precision_score(y_true, y_prob)

    plt.figure()
    plt.plot(recall, precision, label=f"AP={ap:.4f}")
    plt.title("Precision-Recall Curve")
    plt.xlabel("Recall")
    plt.ylabel("Precision")
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(out_path, dpi=200)
    plt.show()
    return ap

pr_path = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, f"{best_model_name}_pr.png")

import math
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import random
from PIL import Image

def predict_one(image_path, model, tfm):
    model.eval()

    img = Image.open(image_path).convert("RGB")
    x = tfm(img).unsqueeze(0).to(device)

    with torch.no_grad():
        logits = model(x)
        probs = F.softmax(logits, dim=1).cpu().numpy()[0]
        pred_class = probs.argmax()

    return {
        "pred": pred_class,
        "probs": probs
    }

def save_prediction_grid(image_paths, model, tfm, out_path, cols=4):
    rows = math.ceil(len(image_paths)/cols)
    plt.figure(figsize=(cols*4, rows*4))

    for i, p in enumerate(image_paths):
        img = Image.open(p).convert("RGB")
        pred = predict_one(p, model, tfm)
        true = os.path.basename(os.path.dirname(p))

        plt.subplot(rows, cols, i+1)
        plt.imshow(img)
        plt.axis("off")
        plt.title(f"T:{true}  P:{pred['pred']}\nPneu:{pred['probs'][1]:.3f}")

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(out_path, dpi=200)
    plt.show()

# Create list of all test image paths (INSERT THIS)
all_test = [path for path, label in test_loader.dataset.base.samples]

print("Total test images:", len(all_test))

# Pick 12 random test images
grid_paths = random.sample(all_test, k=min(12, len(all_test)))
grid_path = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, f"{best_model_name}_sample_predictions.png")
save_prediction_grid(grid_paths, model, val_tfms, grid_path)
print("Saved:", grid_path)
